0bank%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-earnings-q1-jamie-dimon-economy-trump-tariffs-inflation-recession-2025-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DJPMorgan%2527s%2520net%2520revenue%2520rose%25208%2Cciting%2520a%2520worse%2520macroeconomic%2520outlook.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetter-than-expected%20results%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20three%20months%20ending%20March%2031%2C%20but%20all%20eyes%20were%20on%20what%20bank%20execs%20might%20have%20gleaned%20about%20the%20economy%20since%20Trump's%20tariff%20policies%20went%20into%20effect%20on%20April%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-ceo-jamie-dimons-annual-letter-to-investors-stagflation-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20upon%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20finish%20negotiating%20trade%20deals%20and%20get%20it%20done%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%20And%20when%20asked%20how%20the%20current%20economic%20and%20political%20situation%20compares%20to%20the%20past%2C%20Dimon%20said%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20different.%20This%20is%20the%20global%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20response%20to%20an%20analyst's%20question.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20me%20is%20the%20Western%20world%20stays%20together%20economically%2C%20when%20we%20get%20through%20all%20this%2C%20and%20militarily%2C%20to%20keep%20the%20world%20safe%20and%20free%20for%20democracy.%20That%20is%20the%20most%20important%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cb88b05-12c9-4b76-9676-9b6297a8238c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsumer%20spending%20patterns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20financial%20officer%20Jeremy%20Barnum%20described%20an%20economy%20that%20is%20still%20intact%20but%20bracing%20for%20trouble%20ahead.%20Consumers%20are%20still%20spending%2C%20but%20some%20of%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bfront-loading%20spending%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20tariffs%2C%20Barnum%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnother%20thing%20that%20we%20are%20seeing%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20April%20data%2C%20would%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20front-loading%20of%20spending%2C%20specifically%20in%20items%20that%20might%20have%20prices%20go%20up%20as%20a%20function%20of%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20Barnum%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20saw%20some%20weakened%20spending%20among%20lower-income%20consumers%20but%20%26quot%3Bno%20evidence%20of%20distress.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20Barnum%20said%2C%20some%20of%20the%20increases%20in%20April%20spending%20were%20driven%20by%20lower-income%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarnum%20also%20said%20the%20bank%20has%20seen%20a%20dip%20in%20spending%20on%20travel%20but%20was%20reluctant%20to%20draw%20conclusions%20about%20whether%20this%20suggests%20a%20tightening%20of%20the%20purse%20strings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20obvious%20to%20us%20that%20that's%20necessarily%20an%20indicator%20for%20broader%20patterns%2C%26quot%3B%20Barnum%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20variety%20of%20potential%20explanations%20for%20the%20narrow%20drop%20in%20airline%20spend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224078cc8-0aa2-4765-9a80-bf646afa18a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoans%20and%20liquidity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20boosted%20the%20amount%20it%20sets%20aside%20for%20credit%20losses%20by%20%24973%20million%20to%20%243.3%20billion%2C%20citing%20a%20worse%20macroeconomic%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarnum%20said%20JPMorgan%20is%20not%20yet%20seeing%20a%20deterioration%20of%20lending%20quality%2C%20and%20loans%20are%20still%20being%20paid%20at%20the%20expected%20rate.%20Still%2C%20the%20bank%20is%20building%20reserves%20of%20%24441%20million%20for%20consumer%20lending%20and%20%24549%20million%20for%20wholesale%20lending%20to%20protect%20against%20people%20and%20companies%20not%20paying%20their%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarnum%20sa